Freehold New Jersey (PRWEB) October 05, 2015
From October 12th through October 23rd distractiongraphics.com an e-commerce, company that specializes in environmental graphics for glass, will host their 2nd annual Fall Food-Drive to benefit the FoodBank of Monmouth and Ocean Counties. Distractiongraphics.com will be collecting nonperishable food at their manufacturing facility located at 800 Business Park Drive, Freehold NJ 07728. Distractiongraphics.com will match every pound of food collected with a $1.00 donation to the Foodbank of Monmouth and Ocean Counties .
There are 131,000 people living in Monmouth and Ocean Counties struggle with hunger.
That means one out of every ten people in these counties receive “emergency” food from the FoodBank’s network of pantries.
Donating to the distractiongraphics.com Fall Food Drive will directly impact the communities of Monmouth and Ocean Counties. Your contribution will be magnified by distractiongraphics.com dollar per pound of food donation match. That dollar match can provide an additional three meals of food for the FoodBank to distribute to those in need.
Please come out and support this food drive by donating the following suggested items:
Canned tuna, chicken, salmon, fruits, vegetables, beans, peas, lentils, unsweetened applesauce, rice, pasta, peanut butter, jelly, cereals, ready-to-eat canned meals, cooking oils.
For more information on the distractiongraphics.com 2nd annual Fall Food Drive, please visit their Facebook event page at distractiongraphics.com Fall Food Drive .
